# Islamic Glassmorphism Re-Design

Based on the original reference architecture you shared (`https://mnm.miraiznlabs.com/...`), I will execute a complete visual overhaul. I will strip out the "dark green arch" motif and transition the app to the ultra-premium bright frosted-glass aesthetic found in your reference, while gracefully weaving in our interactive capabilities.

## 1. Ditching the "Dark Arch" for "Frosted Glass" (`index.css` & Components)
* **Remove Arch Restraints:** I will remove the `arch-frame` entirely from `HeroCover`, `InsideDetails`, and `RSVPForm`. 
* **Classic Glassmorphism Base:** UI blocks will become beautiful, modern rounded rectangles (`rounded-3xl` or `rounded-2xl`) featuring heavy frost (`backdrop-blur-md bg-white/70 shadow-[0_8px_30px_rgb(0,0,0,0.08)]`).
* **Background Change:** I will strip out the heavy dark `body` background and replace it with the bright Cream/Warm Ivory (`#F5F4F0`). We will blend an ultra-subtle, light-toned Islamic geometric lattice or subtle neutral floral texture behind the blur.

## 2. Text Color Inversion
* Since the cards will now be milky translucent white (frosted glass), all typography must invert.
* **Headers (Cormorant):** Will shift from bright white to Deep Charcoal (`#1F2937`) or rich Sage Green (`#4A5D4E`).
* **Accents (Inter):** Will shift from Gold to muted Taupe (`#8C8273`).
* **Bismillah & Motifs:** These will remain as central ornate figures, but painted in soft gold or deep charcoal over the frosted glass.

## 3. Reference Feature: "Pill Badges" & Layouts
* I will implement the tiny "exclusive invitation" pill-badges seen on the reference site.
* The content hierarchy will be optimized to be highly spacious within the frosted squares.

## 4. Reference Feature: RSVP "Choice Tiles"
* I will alter `RSVPForm.jsx` from standard drop-downs or simple buttons into the spectacular large, touch-friendly, square "Choice Tiles" (big icon squares to select "Attending" or "Declining" that sit gracefully on the glass).

## 5. Map Embed & Envelope Update
* **Venue Map:** It will be expanded beautifully within its own frosted module.
* **Envelope SVG:** We will keep the physical opening animation, but invert its colors so it perfectly matches the new luxurious light-toned aesthetic.

